ary%20Affairs%20Minister%20Jogaram%20Patel%20used%20%26quot%3Bunparliamentary%26quot%3B%20language%20in%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Patel%20made%20the%20remarks%20during%20the%20Question%20Hour%2C%20which%20became%20a%20bone%20of%20contention%20when%20the%20house%20resumed%20after%20lunch%20for%20debate%20on%20the%20Governor's%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20settled%20when%20Mr%20Patel%20apologised%20saying%20he%20did%20not%20mean%20to%20use%20the%20word.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20occurred%20during%20a%20discussion%2C%20when%20Minister%20Otaram%20Dewasi%20was%20replying%20to%20the%20question%20raised%20by%20Congress%20MLA%20Chetan%20Patel%20related%20to%20crop%20damage%20due%20to%20floods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeader%20of%20Opposition%20Tikaram%20Jully%20expressed%20his%20displeasure%20over%20the%20minister's%20answer%20and%20asked%20counter%20questions%2C%20leading%20to%20an%20uproar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20Mr%20Jully%20asked%20the%20minister%20to%20give%20the%20figures%20of%20damage%20in%20Sangod%20of%20Kota%2C%20Mr%20Patel%20stood%20up%20and%20used%20an%20abusive%20word.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20soon%20as%20the%20House%20resumed%20after%20lunch%2C%20Congress%20state%20president%20Govind%20Singh%20Dotasra%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20House%20was%20in%20session.%20When%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20was%20speaking%2C%20the%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20Minister%20objected%20to%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition.%20He%20did%20not%20only%20objected%2C%20but%20also%20abused.%20There%20can%20be%20nothing%20more%20unfortunate%20than%20this.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20can%20be%20more%20shameful%20that%20the%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20Minister%20abusing%3F%20We%20come%20here%20for%20the%20issues%20of%20the%20common%20people%2C%20we%20do%20not%20come%20here%20to%20be%20abused.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Patel%20responded%20by%20saying%20he%20and%20his%20party%20always%20respected%20and%20honoured%20the%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20present%20our%20point%20effectively%2C%20we%20do%20not%20lack%20in%20this.%20There%20was%20no%20intention%20to%20hurt%20anyone's%20dignity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20had%20the%20intention%20to%20speak%20unparliamentary%20words%20in%20the%20House%20nor%20will%20I%20have%20in%20the%20future.%20If%20someone%20gets%20excited%20while%20speaking%20in%20the%20flow%2C%20there%20was%20no%20such%20intention.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20should%20be%20deleted%20and%20such%20feelings%20will%20never%20be%20there%20towards%20any%20member%20in%20future.%20I%20feel%20sorry%20for%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Dotasra%20reacted%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20came%20in%20the%20record%2C%20then%20an%20apology%20should%20be%20made.%20Our%20Dhariwal%20ji%20had%20apologised%2C%20I%20had%20apologised%20on%20his%20behalf%2C%20you%20are%20the%20Law%20Minister.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Patel%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20not%20said%20this%20and%20if%20I%20have%20said%20it%2C%20then%20I%20feel%20sorry.%20We%20do%20not%20remain%20adamant%20like%20you.%20We%20respect%20everyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20Speaker%20Vasudev%20Devnani%20directed%20the%20members%20to%20maintain%20decorum%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20something%20goes%20wrong%2C%20we%20should%20immediately%20take%20action%20against%20it.%20If%20something%20happens%20then%20I%20think%20there%20is%20no%20harm%20in%20apologising%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20House%20proceeded%20for%20debate%20on%20the%20Governor's%20address%20and%20adjourned%20till%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738603500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fun8